    "explanation": "<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 20th July Evening Shift Chemistry - IUPAC Nomenclatures Question 1 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnla64l7/ba9704d3-3e66-4b7e-bd54-247552260bb9/9ca468b0-30aa-11f1-9940-770035a03727/file-jaoe38c1mnla64l8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnla64l7/ba9704d3-3e66-4b7e-bd54-247552260bb9/9ca468b0-30aa-11f1-9940-770035a03727/file-jaoe38c1mnla64l8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p><p>Tertiary amines have three alkyl groups attached to - N . The parent chain is selected with the highest number of -C atoms. Other alkyl groups are treated as substituents (in this case methyl and ethyl). While naming, the suffix ' e ' of arene is replaced by 'amine' and locant N is written before each substituent name (which follows alphabetical order).</p><p></p>\n<p>∴ The IUPAC name will be N -ethyl-N-methylbenzenamine.</p>",
